  "prompt": "What is a good inpatient drug and alcohol rehab center near Fayette County IN?",
  "response": "While I cannot provide real-time recommendations or the latest information, I can suggest a few types of resources to find inpatient drug and alcohol rehab centers near Fayette County, IN:\n\n1. **Local Hospitals and Healthcare Providers:** Contact local hospitals or healthcare providers for recommendations on rehabilitation centers.\n\n2. **Substance Abuse and Mental Health Services Administration (SAMHSA):** SAMHSA offers a national helpline and an online treatment locator that can help you find facilities. Their website is: [samhsa.gov](https://www.samhsa.gov).\n\n3. **State Health Departments:** Indiana's state health department may have resources and lists of licensed treatment facilities in your area.\n\n4. **Community Resources:** Local community health organizations or support groups might have valuable information on rehab centers.\n\n5. **Online Directories:** Websites like Psychology Today, Rehab.com, or AddictionCenter.com allow you to search for facilities based on your criteria.\n\nEnsure that any facility you consider is accredited and offers a program that aligns with your needs. It's also advisable to contact the center directly to ask about their treatment options, costs, and insurance coverage.",
